Polynomials and
Negative Powers
Before you divide one polynomial by another polynomial, you need to
know how to write the multiplicative inverse of a polynomial.
Finding the Reciprocal of a Polynomial
The reciprocal of a polynomial is its multiplicative inverse.
To find the reciprocal of Polynomial A, you divide the number 1 by
Polynomial A.
Example 1
Find the reciprocal of each of these polynomials:
a) 2x - 1
b) -5x² + 3x - 1
